# archive.sqlite is rematerialized by `state status` / `summary` and is not
# the source of truth — it's a perf cache that the streaming-ledger fallback
# (RELAYBURN_ARCHIVE=0) can rebuild on demand. Keeping the binary out of git
# means snapshot regeneration doesn't churn a multi-KB blob on every run.
#
# burn.sqlite + content.sqlite are also rematerialized — the Rust diff
# runner replays `ledger.jsonl` into them on first run (the Rust SDK is
# sqlite-only) and the TS CLI uses the file adapter, so neither needs the
# blobs in git.
archive.sqlite
archive.sqlite-shm
archive.sqlite-wal
burn.sqlite
burn.sqlite-shm
burn.sqlite-wal
content.sqlite
content.sqlite-shm
content.sqlite-wal
cursors.json
hwm.json
config.json
